<h3 id="1-using-yarn">1. Using yarn</h3>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>$ sudo npm install -g yarn
$ sudo yarn global add elm
</code></pre></div></div>

<h3 id="2-npmì˜-ì„¤ì¹˜-í´ë”ë¥¼-ë°”ê¾¼ë‹¤--change-npm-global-install-folder-docsnpmjs">2. npmì˜ ì„¤ì¹˜ í´ë”ë¥¼ ë°”ê¾¼ë‹¤ | Change npm-global install folder <a href="https://docs.npmjs.com/getting-started/fixing-npm-permissions">docs.npmjs</a></h3>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>$ mkdir ~/.npm-global
$ npm config set prefix '~/.npm-global'
$ echo 'export PATH=~/.npm-global/bin:$PATH' &gt;&gt; ~/.profile
$ source ~/.profile
$ npm install -g elm
</code></pre></div></div>
